<para>
  <classname>DisplayMethods</classname> are the techniques used to
  draw the &oof2; objects, such as <link
  linkend='Section-Concepts-Microstructure-Image'>Images</link> and
  <link linkend='Section-Concepts-Skeleton'>Skeletons</link>, in the
  <link linkend='Chapter-Graphics'>Graphics Window</link>.  Each <link
  linkend='Section-Graphics-Layer'>Layer</link> in the Graphics Window
  corresponds to a single <classname>DisplayMethod</classname>.
</para>

<para>
  <classname>DisplayMethods</classname> may take parameters, which are
  described in the sections for each specific method. These parameters
  govern things like line widths, colors,
  <foreignphrase>etc</foreignphrase>.  One thing that the parameters
  do <emphasis>not</emphasis> govern is the object (&image;, &mesh;,
  <foreignphrase>etc.</foreignphrase>) which the
  <classname>DisplayMethod</classname> displays.  That is determined
  by the <varname>category</varname> and <varname>what</varname>
  parameters in the <link linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Graphics_n.Layer.New">
  new layer</link> or <link
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Graphics_n.Layer.Edit">edit layer</link>
  commands.
</para>

